'''[[geometric]] [[isomerism]]'''
#{{chemistry}} a form of isomerism in which, in one [[isomer]] two [[atom]]s or [[group]]s are on the [[same]] [[side]] of the [[plane]] of a [[double bond]] or [[ring]], whereas in the [[other]] isomer they are on [[opposite]] sides; the first is the [[cis-]] and the second the [[trans-]] isomer
